result.execSummary:
The defendant Robert S Swanton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 1st-Degree Intentional Homicide [Modifiers: Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class A felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.01(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Eligible for extended supervision after serving 40 years.
Court costs are waived. Defendant must submit a DNA sample as required by law and must pay mandatory DNA surcharge.
Firearm warning given. Voting prohibited until sentence is complete and civil rights have been restored. Defendant must obey all rules and regulations of probation.

AMENDED TO ADD RESTITUTION AS DETERMINED BY STIPULATION

It is the court's intention that the Department of Corrections can take 25% from all money received for the benefit of the inmate while he is incarcerated to be applied to restitution owing to the victim.
